namedLocations.description: Ahmedabad (/ˈəhmədɑːbɑːd/ is the largest city and former capital of the Indian state of Gujarat. namedLocations.description: Alaska (/əˈlæskə/ ; Aleut: Alax̂sxax̂; Inupiaq: Alaasikaq; Alutiiq: Alas'kaaq; Tlingit: Anáaski; Russian: Аляска, romanized: Alyaska) is a U.S. state in the northwest extremity of the United States West Coast, just across the Bering Strait from Asia. The Canadian province of British Columbia and territory of Yukon border the state to the east and southeast. Its most extreme western part is Attu Island, and it has a maritime border with Russia (Chukotka Autonomous Okrug) to the west across the Bering Strait. To the north are the Chukchi and Beaufort seas—southern parts of the Arctic Ocean. The Pacific Ocean lies to the south and southwest. It is the largest U.S. state by area and the seventh largest subnational division in the world. In addition, it is the 3rd least populous and the most sparsely populated of the 50 United States; nevertheless, it is by far the most populous territory located mostly north of the 60th parallel in North America: its population—estimated at 738,432 by the United States Census Bureau in 2015— is more than quadruple the combined populations of Northern Canada and Greenland. Approximately half of Alaska's residents live within the Anchorage metropolitan area. Alaska's economy is dominated by the fishing, natural gas, and oil industries, resources which it has in abundance. United States armed forces bases and tourism are also a significant part of the economy.
namedLocations.name: Alaska

namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.
namedLocations.name: ZIP Code

The density of Mishra is more among Saryupareen Brahmins, Kanyakubja Brahmins, utkala brahmin,Sakaldwipi Brahmins, Maithil Brahmins, Bhumihar Brahmins, Utkala Brahmins and Upadhaya Brahmins in Nepal. It is one of the most widespread Brahmin surnames in the fertile Gangetic plain region and in the Indian states of Delhi, Bihar, Uttar Pradesh, Odisha, Uttarakhand, Madhya Pradesh, Rajasthan, Assam, Hyderabad, and West Bengal. It is also found in countries such as Guyana and Trinidad and Tobago under the anglicized version of Misir, The surname is also found in Nepal, Fiji and Mauritius, as well as in other Indian diaspora communities. "Mishra" or Misra is similar to Maitreya or mapasa or Maitra or Maitri Mishra and both have same meaning. It is also found in countries such as Guyana and Trinidad and Tobago under the anglicized version of Misir, where many Mishras were taken to work on sugar plantations due to their agricultural prowess and skills in medical fields. The surname is also found in Fiji and Mauritius, as well as in other Indian diaspora communities.

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to on Print shop.
In this video, we will have a look at Ship to multiple addresses.
We have introduced a new feature called Ship to multiple address which allows users to create multiple shipments in a single order.
Let's go to the admin, click on store configuration, go to site settings and search Ship to in the search bar as you can see here.
After that you can see four types of new settings we have added.
1st is Enable ship to multiple address where we have options available as None, Default store, All private slash public store and both.
You can see the details here.
Second we have shipped to multiple address option on cart page where we have option to disable always and optional.
Third we have enable split quantity and ship to multiple address.
In this you have to choose Yes or no.
Last setting we have is display product groups title and Ship to multiple address.
In this we have none, default and vendor.
To enable one setting for a vendor, you have to go to business partners, then click on Printers, then action and edit.
Here we have group products and checkout page.
Enable it and save.
Now let's go to the storefront and customer shopping cart.
Here we can see there are two products in the shopping cart and here we have a new option Ship to multiple address.
You can hide by choosing to disable this setting.
You can show separately by choosing optional or you can merge multiple shipping with the continue button by choosing the always setting in the admin here.
After that when we proceed further by clicking on the ship to multiple address button.
Here we can see two types of product groups.
So if you have assigned any product to a vendor or printer then here you will see those products in a group with a vendor name in the admin setting.
You have to choose the vendor here.
For products which are not assigned to any vendor, those will appear in the default group name which is the admin.
You can change the title from language text references as you can see here.

Also if you choose the default in the Display product group setting then at the front end system will show the product group name as default name with a number for example product group number one, product group number 2 and if you choose none then there will be no product group name display.
It will only show separate products which are not assigned or assigned vendor wise.
Next we have an option where you can split quantity as well for each product in the shopping cart and then create multiple shipments to multiple addresses.
For example here we are splitting quantity in two parts that is 50 quantities at one address and another 50 quantities at another address.
After creating a shipment, you can see the summary of all the shipments on the right hand side.
Also, you will not see the continue button to proceed until and unless you have created all the shipments for the products in the shopping cart without any quantity left.
You can modify your shipments as well by clicking on the edit icon and can change the address or quantity.
After you have created all the shipments, you can see the continue button to proceed and then we can check out further like a normal process.
Once the order has been placed, the customer can see his entire shipment summary under Shipping details.
Now in the admin section under the View Order details page, you will be able to see all the shipment details as you can see over here.
Also, when you click on Modify Order, you can see a new option Manage Ship to Multiple Address here.
You can modify your existing shipment by clicking on Modify icon and split the quantity for multiple addresses.
You can create a new shipment for a new order product that you want to add to this order.
After adding a new order shipment to the existing order, as you can see over here on the view order page, you will be able to see the new shipment detail as well which we have added to this order.

Now if we talk about the invoice and job ticket, you can modify both e-mail formats and can add a variable named ship to multiple address details so when we download them you can see multiple address details in both.
The next feature we have in export API orders go to API settings.
Here we can see Ship to multiple address info for export.
It is available in the API services as well to export multiple address shipment report in Jason or XML format.
Also in coupon discount, whenever you add a coupon, you can choose conditional discount based on cart subtotal.
Then the discount will be applied on each shipment total.
In case of Ship to multiple addresses selected at the front end, it will not work on the cart subtotal price in that case.
These are all the new features in the ship to multiple addresses.
Thank you for watching this video.
In case of any further concerns, feel free to connect with us.
